---

Interview-Style Summary

Concept	Purpose	React Tool

TanStack Query	Manage server state and API calls	useQuery, useMutation
Lazy Loading	Load component only when needed	React.lazy()
Code Splitting	Split bundle into chunks	import() + bundler
Suspense	Show fallback during lazy load	<Suspense>
Query Cache	Avoid unnecessary requests	queryKey
Mutation	Create/Update/Delete data	useMutation
Route Splitting	Load route code on navigation	React.lazy() + Router


A common production setup is: React Router + React.lazy (for route-level code splitting) + TanStack Query (for API caching and synchronization). This combination significantly improves both initial load performance and data-fetching efficiency.
